o breast cancer outcomes through social determinants of health. Structural racism includes residential segregation and racial bias. Social determinants cover economic factors, housing, education, healthcare access, and\ social context. Breast cancer outcomes are incidence, diagnosis stage, mortality, tissue biomarkers, and screening rates, with process measures like care receipt and patient stress levels.)/K 0/P 1107 0 R/Pg 238 0 R/S/Figure/T()>>endobj1119 0 obj<</BBox 1120 0 R/Height 340.657/O/Layout/Width 451.435>>endobj1120 0 obj[72.033 406.749 523.468 747.406]endobj1121 0 obj<</A 1122 0 R/ActualText(Flowchart illustrating the study selection process. Initial studies from databases: 466 \(PubMed 451, Embase 13, CINAHL 2\). References removed: 262 \(0 manually, 262 by Covidence, 0 by automation\). Studies screened: 204. Studies excluded: 123.)/Alt(Flowchart illustrating the study selection process. Initial studies from databases: 466 \(PubMed 451, Embase 13, CINAHL 2\). References removed: 262 \(0 manually, 262 by Covidence, 0 by automation\). Studies screened: 204. Studies excluded: 123.)/K 0/P 1107 0 R/Pg 43 0 R/S/Figure/T()>>endobj1122 0 obj<</BBox 1123 0 R/Height 443.215/O/Layout/Width 341.735>>endobj1123 0 obj[126.912 303.964 468.647 747.179]endobj1124 0 obj<</Author(Ola Abdelhadi)/CreationDate(D:20250716165352+08'00')/Keywords(breast cancer; structural racism; SDOH; quality of care; cancer care)/ModDate(D:20250716165352+08'00')/Subject(Abdelhadi O, Williams M and Yan A \(2025\) Structural racism as a leading cause of racial disparities in breast cancer quality of care outcomes: a systematic review. Front. Oncol. 15:1562672. doi: 10.3389/fonc.2025.1562672)/Title(Structural racism as a leading cause of racial disparities in breast cancer quality of care outcomes: a systematic review)>>endobjxref
